# 🌆 Urban Pollution & Human Health Monitor

Real-time AQI web app using **US EPA breakpoints** (0–500 scale), rich health advisories, and detailed preventive measures per pollution level.

---

## ✅ Fixes in This Version

| Issue | Fix Applied |
|---|---|
| AQI in single digits | Now calculated using **US EPA formula** from PM2.5 & O3 concentrations — gives real 0–500 AQI |
| No preventive measures | Full **preventive measures grid** with 4–9 actionable steps per AQI level |
| Sensitive groups missing | Dedicated **sensitive groups** section (children, elderly, pregnant, heart/lung patients) |
| UI not appealing | Complete redesign — dark navy + teal, Bebas Neue typography, editorial dashboard layout |

---

## 🚀 Run Locally

1. Open folder in **VS Code**
2. Install **Live Server** extension
3. Right-click `index.html` → **Open with Live Server**
4. Opens at `http://127.0.0.1:5500`

> Geolocation requires localhost or HTTPS — Live Server handles this.

---

## ☁️ Deploy to GitHub Pages

```bash
git init && git add .
git commit -m "Urban Pollution Monitor"
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USER/YOUR_REPO.git
git push -u origin main
```
Then: **Settings → Pages → Branch: main → Save**

Live URL: `https://YOUR_USER.github.io/YOUR_REPO/`

---

## 🎨 AQI Scale (US EPA)

| AQI | Category | Color | Key Action |
|---|---|---|---|
| 0–50 | Good | 🟢 Green | No restrictions |
| 51–100 | Moderate | 🟡 Yellow | Sensitive groups reduce exertion |
| 101–150 | Unhealthy for Sensitive | 🟠 Orange | Wear mask, limit outdoor time |
| 151–200 | Unhealthy | 🔴 Red | Avoid outdoor activity |
| 201–300 | Very Unhealthy | 🟣 Purple | Stay indoors, seal building |
| 301+ | Hazardous | 🔴 Dark Red | Emergency protocol |

Data: OpenWeatherMap · AQI: US EPA formula from PM2.5 & O3
